727111f-a.text:
Junction Boulevard, at the S.W. corner of 37th Avenue, showing the Leverich house and a barn that was used as a fish store.  Annie F. Leverich owned this property in 1909.  Members of the Leverich family owned extensive tracts of land in this area with numerous farm buildings.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
About 1922

727112f-a.text:
Junction Boulevard, (rear of dilapidated barn; trolley cars thereon) at the S.W. corner of Thirty-seventh Avenue (right of barn).  The building in the foreground was Fish's store and is at the S.W. corner of the above locations.  It was demolished on Oct. 1, 1925.

March 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
